725018f-a.title: Queens: 12th Street - North 27th Avenue.
725018f-a.text:
12th Street, east side, north from 27th Avenue, showing
a row of private homes of a type most fashionable at the
turn of the century. The first house was owned by a member
of the Blackwell family,
View 2 shows the Blackwell house.
P. L. Sperr  March 11, 1931

725017f-a.title: Queens: 12th Street - North 27th Avenue.
725017f-a.text:
12th Street, east side, north from 27th Avenue,showing a row
of fashionable homes. The corner house is a Blackwell house,
having been owned by R. M. Blackwell in 1873. The other homes
were the property of C. R. Trafford. 12th Street was formerly
Remsen Street.
P. L. Sperr  June 2, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS

725157f-a.title: Queens: 27th Avenue - 12th Street
725157f-a.text:
97th Avenue, at, and adjoining the N. W. corner of 12th Street.
The corner house was built by Dr. Taylor (according to P. L. Sperr)
about a century ago and has always been eccupied by aen of the
same profession.
View 1: P. L. Sperr  March 11, 1931
NO REPRODUCTIONS
View 2: George D. Chinn  April 26, 1940
